HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 180
BY REPRESENTATIVE SPELL
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates April 22, 2026, as Counseling Day at the
Capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, April 22, 2026, as Counseling Day at the Capitol and to commend
3 the Louisiana Counseling Association for its outstanding contributions to the citizens
4 of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, Counseling Day at the Capitol serves as an important occasion to
6 highlight the essential role that professional counselors play in strengthening the mental
7 health and well-being of individuals, families, and communities throughout Louisiana; and
8 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Counseling Association is a leading organization
9 dedicated to advancing the counseling profession, supporting licensed counselors, and
10 promoting access to high quality mental health services across the state; and
11 WHEREAS, professional counselors work diligently to address a wide range of
12 challenges including anxiety, depression, trauma, substance abuse, and family-related issues,
13 helping individuals cope with life's most difficult circumstances; and
14 WHEREAS, through compassion, expertise, and a commitment to service, counselors
15 provide safe and supportive environments where Louisianians can find comfort, healing, and
16 peace of mind; and
17 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Counseling Association advocates for policies that
18 expand access to mental health care, reduce the stigmas associated with counseling, and
19 ensure that individuals in all communities receive the support they need; and
20 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Counseling Association is most deserving of the highest
21 recognition for its invaluable contributions to the people of this state.
